The article discusses the devastating toll of climate change, including hurricanes, floods, wildfires, and record temperatures. The Biden Administration has taken action to tackle the climate crisis by securing the largest climate investment in history, promoting clean energy, advancing environmental justice, and rallying world leaders. The administration has announced a temporary pause on pending decisions of Liquefied Natural Gas exports to assess their impact on energy costs, energy security, and the environment. The article emphasizes the urgency of the climate crisis and the need for action, despite opposition from some Republicans. The administration aims to create clean energy jobs and build a more hopeful future for children.